{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2012"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of fertilizers and nitrogen compounds"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2012"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :fertilizers-nitrogen-compounds/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :environmental-safety :materials-safety :resource-efficiency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :fertilizer-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae :cfd]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "FertAdvisor ⊣ Fertilizer Plant Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for fertilizer-and-nitrogen-compound manufacturing (ammonia
 synthesis / granulation lines producing straight nitrogen fertilizers,
 phosphate fertilizers and blended N-P-K compound fertilizers) -- an
 upstream chemical-process plant with a real explosion/toxic-release
 hazard profile -- not direct ammonia-synthesis/granulation-line
 control authority. Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Ten concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct synthesis/granulation-line-equipment control),
 permanent line-actuate block, independent equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-weight recompute against the batch's own logged
 weight, double-schedule guard, product-grade validation, and
 nutrient-content (N-P-K) label plausibility validation.
 Safety-concern flagging (ammonia-exposure/ammonium-nitrate-explosion-
 risk/environmental-hazard/equipment-safety) ALWAYS escalates to a
 human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op
 eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
